                    <h3 class="mb-1 text-primary">Basics of Crypto Trading & Risk Management</h3>
                    <img src="~/assets/images/basics.jpeg" class="img-fluid my-3 rounded" alt="Basics of Crypto Trading & Risk Management" />
                </div>

                <h6 class="fw-medium mb-3 text-primary">Introduction</h6>
                <p class="mb-3">
                    This guide provides a high-level overview of cryptocurrency trading and essential risk management strategies. Whether you're just starting out or looking to refresh your understanding, the sections below outline core principles to help you navigate the crypto market more confidently.
                </p>

                <h6 class="fw-medium mb-3 text-primary">1. What is Crypto Trading?</h6>
                <ul class="terms-list list-unstyled">
                    <li>
                        <p class="mb-0">
                            Crypto trading involves buying and selling digital assets like Bitcoin, Ethereum, and other altcoins. Traders aim to profit from market fluctuations by entering and exiting positions at optimal times. It can be done through spot markets (buying actual coins) or derivatives (futures, options).
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h6 class="fw-medium mb-3 text-primary">2. Key Trading Concepts</h6>
                <ul class="terms-list list-unstyled">
                    <li>
                        <div class="fs-14 fw-medium">a. Market Orders vs. Limit Orders</div>
                        <p class="mb-0">A market order buys/sells immediately at current prices, while a limit order executes only at your set price.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <div class="fs-14 fw-medium">b. Support & Resistance</div>
                        <p class="mb-0">Support is a price level where buying tends to happen. Resistance is where selling pressure occurs. Recognizing these can guide entries and exits.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <div class="fs-14 fw-medium">c. Candlestick Charts</div>
                        <p class="mb-0">These charts display price movement over time and help identify market sentiment and patterns.</p>
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h6 class="fw-medium mb-3 text-primary">3. Risk Management</h6>
                <ul class="terms-list list-unstyled">
                    <li>
                        <div class="fs-14 fw-medium">a. Only Risk What You Can Afford to Lose</div>
                        <p class="mb-0">Crypto is volatile. Never invest more than you can afford to lose.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <div class="fs-14 fw-medium">b. Use Stop-Loss Orders</div>
                        <p class="mb-0">Stop-loss orders automatically close your trade at a certain price to prevent major losses.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <div class="fs-14 fw-medium">c. Diversify</div>
                        <p class="mb-0">Avoid putting all your funds into a single coin. Diversifying reduces exposure to one asset's risk.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <div class="fs-14 fw-medium">d. Don't Chase the Market</div>
                        <p class="mb-0">Avoid FOMO (Fear of Missing Out) trades. Emotional decisions usually lead to poor outcomes.</p>
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h6 class="fw-medium mb-3 text-primary">4. Tools & Resources</h6>
                <ul class="terms-list list-unstyled mb-3">
                    <li>
                        <p class="mb-0">
                            Beginners are encouraged to use paper trading platforms to practice without risking real money. Consider also learning from charting platforms like TradingView, and following reputable educational YouTube channels or blogs.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h6 class="fw-medium mb-3 text-primary">Final Thoughts</h6>
                <p class="mb-0">
                    Crypto trading carries both opportunities and risks. Take your time, build your knowledge, and prioritize managing your downside. Treat it like a long-term learning journey rather than a get-rich-quick scheme.
                </p>
